data.chText: 拇指
data.enText: the short thick finger at the side of the hand, slightly apart from the other four

data.chText: 她在忧虑时仍然会吸吮大拇指。
data.enText: She still sucks her thumb when she's worried.

data.chText: （手套的）拇指部分
data.enText: the part of a glove that covers the thumb

data.chText: 手套的拇指上有个窟窿。
data.enText: There's a hole in the thumb.
be all (fingers and) thumbs

data.chText: 笨手笨脚；笨拙；手指不灵活
data.enText: to be awkward with your hands so that you drop things or are unable to do sth
hold thumbs

data.chText: 希望（计划）成功；期望如愿以偿
data.enText: to hope that your plans will be successful or that sth will take place in the way that you want it to

data.chText: 我们期望你如愿得到这份工作啊。
data.enText: Let's hold thumbs that you get the job.
thumbs up/down

data.chText: 翘拇指（表示接受或成功）；拇指向下（表示拒绝或不成功）
data.enText: used to show that sth has been accepted/rejected or that it is/is not a success

data.chText: 他们的建议遭到拒绝。
data.enText: Their proposals were given the thumbs down .

data.chText: 看样子他们的最新歌曲专辑成功了。
data.enText: It looks like it's thumbs up for their latest album.

data.chText: 在古罗马的角斗中，公众若希望角斗士活就竖起拇指朝上，若希望他被杀死就伸出拇指朝下。
data.enText: In contests in ancient Rome the public put their thumbs up if they wanted a gladiator to live, and down if they wanted him to be killed.
under sb's thumb

data.chText: 完全受人支配；受制于人
data.enText: completely controlled by sb
a rule of thumb

data.chText: 实用的估算方法，经验工作法（常依据经验而非准确测量）
data.enText: a practical method of doing or measuring sth, usually based on past experience rather than on exact measurement
stand/stick out like a sore thumb

data.chText: 刺眼；扎眼
data.enText: to be very noticeable in an unpleasant way
twiddle your thumbs

data.chText: 抱手旋弄大拇指
data.enText: to move your thumbs around each other with your fingers joined together

data.chText: （等待之际）无所事事
data.enText: to do nothing while you are waiting for sth to happen

data.chText: 翘起拇指请求搭乘（过路汽车）；示意请求搭便车
data.enText: to make a signal with your thumb to passing drivers to ask them to stop and take you somewhere

data.chText: 他搭乘便车游遍了欧洲。
data.enText: He had thumbed all across Europe.

data.chText: 我们设法使得过路的卡车司机允许我们搭便车。
data.enText: We managed to thumb a lift/ride with a truck driver.

data.chText: 用拇指摸；用拇指捋
data.enText: to touch or move sth with your thumb

data.chText: 她用拇指打开了手枪的保险栓。
data.enText: She thumbed off the safety catch of her pistol.
thumb your nose at sb/sth

data.chText: 嗤之以鼻；蔑视
data.enText: to make a rude sign with your thumb on your nose; to show that you have no respect for sb/sth

data.chText: 这家公司完全不把污染立法放在眼里。
data.enText: The company just thumbs its nose at the legislation on pollution.
thumb through sth

data.chText: 快速翻阅
data.enText: to turn the pages of a book quickly in order to get a general idea of what is in it

tr: a convex molding having a cross section in the form of a quarter of a circle or of an ellipse
the part of a glove that provides a covering for the thumb
the thick short innermost digit of the forelimb
feel or handle with the fingers
example: finger the binding of the book

tr: travel by getting free rides from motorists
look through a book or other written material

value.def: Your thumb is the short thick part on the side of your hand next to your four fingers.

example.ex: She bit the tip of her left thumb, not looking at me.
example.tran: 她咬着左手的拇指尖，眼睛也不看我。

value.def: The thumb of a glove is the part which a person's thumb fits into.
If you thumb a lift or thumb a ride, you stand by the side of the road holding out your thumb until a driver stops and gives you a lift.

example.ex: It may interest you to know that a boy answering Rory's description thumbed a ride to Howth...
example.tran: 你或许会对这个消息感兴趣，有个和罗里描述的一模一样的小男孩搭便车到了霍斯。

example.ex: Thumbing a lift had once a carefree, easy-going image.
example.tran: 伸手搭便车曾经给人以轻松随意的形象。

value.tran: (站在路边，伸出手，拇指向上)请求搭便车，拦车

value.def: If you say that someone or something sticks out like a sore thumb or stands out like a sore thumb, you are emphasizing that they are very noticeable, usually because they are unusual or inappropriate.

example.ex: Does the new housing stick out like a sore thumb or blend into its surroundings?...
example.tran: 这个新住宅区是显得有点扎眼，还是和环境融为一体？

example.ex: In Japan a European stands out like a sore thumb.
example.tran: 欧洲人到了日本会极为惹眼。

value.def: If you say that someone is twiddling their thumbs, you mean that they do not have anything to do and are waiting for something to happen.

example.ex: The prospect of waiting around just twiddling his thumbs was appalling...
example.tran: 想到将要无所事事，他就非常害怕。

example.ex: The Government cannot expect graduates to twiddle their thumbs on the dole.
example.tran: 政府不愿意看到毕业生领着救济金却什么也不干。

value.def: If you are under someone's thumb, you are under their control, or very heavily influenced by them.

example.ex: I cannot tell you what pain I feel when I see how much my mother is under my father's thumb...
example.tran: 看见我母亲完完全全受我父亲的控制，我心里别提有多难受。

example.ex: She has Rachel firmly under her thumb.
example.tran: 她把雷切尔牢牢地抓在手心里。

xrse.def: to thumb your nose at someone
